.\" %W% %G%
.TH Dfont 2D D-language
.SH NAME
Dfont \- Selects text fonts to be used on the monitor
.br
.I (D Language Tool)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "Dfont"
.I "font"
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fIDfont\fR allows the user to select use of a specific text font on
the monitor.  The GRASS tool \fIDshow.fonts\fR is a UNIX Bourne
shell macro which names and displays the fonts that can be selected using
\fIDfont\fR.  If no font is specified when using other GRASS tools
that display text, the font type \fIromanp\fR is used by default.
This default font can also be selected by inserting a dash \fB-\fR in
place of a specific font (i.e., \fBDfont -\fR).  Font options are:
.br
.sp
    cyrilc - cyrillic
.br
    gothgbt - Gothic Great Britain triplex
.br
    gothgrt - Gothic German triplex
.br
    gothitt - Gothic Italian triplex
.br
    greekc - Greek complex
.br
    greekcs - Greek complex script
.br
    greekp - Greek plain
.br
    greeks - Greek simplex
.br
    italicc - Italian complex
.br
    italiccs - Italian complex small
.br
    italict - Italian triplex
.br
    romanc - Roman complex
.br
    romancs - Roman complex small
.br
    romand - Roman duplex
.br
    romanp - Roman plain
.br
    romans - Roman simplex
.br
    romant - Roman triplex
.br
    scriptc - Script complex
.br
    scripts - Script simplex

.SH NOTES
The font
.I romans
is the fastest font.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.TS
ll.
\fIDINTRO[2D]\fR	Introduction to the GRASS \fID\fR tools
.br
\fIDshow.fonts[2D]\fR	To list and display available font types
.br
\fIDtext[2D]\fR	To draw text in the current graphics window
.br
\fIDtitle[2D]\fR	Create a title for a grid cell map
.TE
